matches.Rd

A data.frame indicating the OTM that best described the dynamics of a given tile. This data was generated using the match_data function using a flights data set processed using rnp_flights_data with a spatial resolution of 1 m2 (the flights_data object included in throne), an OTM splines tibble generated using gen_otm_splines setting the knot_p = 0.02 built from the otms_data data set that is also included in throne, and by setting error_max = 100 and coverage_per = 0.9.

Usage

matches

Format

A data.frame of 6236 rows and 5 columns

x

A numeric column indicating the horizontal UTM coordinate

y

A numeric column indicating the vertical UTM coordinate

otm_id

A character column indicating the OTM that best describe the dynamics of a tile, a value of NA indicates that that tile could not be matched with any OTM with an error < error_max

error

A numeric column indicating the average absolute error between the thermal dynamics of a tile and the OTM that best described it

coverage

A numeric column indicating the coverage of a tile across all flights
